headline: Southwest Air (LUV) Nosedives 11% on Dismal Earnings, Weak Outlook
summary: We recently published Double-Digit Disaster: 10 Big Names Fall Off the Cliff. Southwest Airlines Co. (NYSE:LUV) is one of the worst-performing stocks on Thursday. Southwest Airlines snapped a four-day winning streak on Thursday, slashing 11.16 percent to close at $33.26 apiece, as investor sentiment was dampened by a dismal earnings performance and a weaker growth outlook.
